subject: Call of Cthulhu fixes
msgSnippet: I ve pushed out another update to  — specifically, Call of Cthulhu. After copy/pasting from a sensibly-generated
messageBody:
I've pushed out another update to <https://github.com/adiabatic/qs-literature> — specifically, Call of Cthulhu. After copy/pasting from a sensibly-generated .odt, I've managed to pinpoint and correct quite a few errors, so you might want to download/reload for this one. The meat of the commit message, for the curious:

- merge lines that aren't really separate paragraphs
- split lines that should be multiple paragraphs (only one)
- correct tw/wt transposition
- blockquote "in his house at R'lyeh dead Cthulhu waits dreaming."
- blockquote "…fthagn"
- blockquote *all* of the "Mystery Derelict Found at Sea" clipping
- un-happy-tense "delicately" — which was in Orthodox in the original

I've also corrected a typo — on line 9 ("My knowledge of the thing…so elderly a man…— and more than wonder") "elderly" is spelled as "enderly".

Incidentally, does "Legrasse's" need a namer dot?
